==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Falcidian
<hw>Fal*cid"i*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Falcidius</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Publius Falcidius,
a Roman tribune.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Falcidian law</b></col> <fld>(Civil Law)</fld>, <cd>a law
by which a testator was obliged to leave at least a fourth of his estate
to the heir.</cd> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Falciform</ent>⟦br⟧
